{"questionId":"22706828","questionHtml":"<p>Hence show that when the T-shirt is launched vertically, the time for it to reach its maximum height is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> seconds.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mn>90</mn><mo>º</mo></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>29</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for setting their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>y</mi><mo>˙</mo></mover></math> to zero (may still include <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>θ</mi></math>), <strong><em>A1</em></strong> for correct equation, leading to given result.<br>If they substitute <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> award at most <em><strong>(A1)M0A0</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>maximum point when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>29</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;(seconds)<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22706828","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ1.2bii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence show that when the T-shirt is launched vertically, the time for it to reach its maximum height is 3 seconds.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrum